<JournalEntry
  title="D439 Pre-Assessment Quiz – Meeting with Dr. Jen Scarpena"
  date="2026-03-22"
  entryType="Pre-Clinical Quiz Day"
  course="D439 – Foundations of Nursing"
  instructor="Dr. Jen Scarpena"
>
  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    This morning I met with <strong>Dr. Jen Scarpena</strong> to complete the required
    online pre-assessment quiz for the <strong>D439 Foundations of Nursing</strong> course.
    The quiz consisted of <strong>10 questions</strong> and must be passed to gain
    permission to sit the D439 course objective assessment (OA).
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    The session took place on <strong>Sunday, March 22, 2026</strong>. Dr. Scarpena
    guided me through the process and confirmed that the quiz is administered online through
    the WGU student portal. Successful completion of this quiz demonstrates foundational
    readiness and is a mandatory prerequisite before the official objective assessment can
    be scheduled.
  </p>
  <p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
    The 10 questions covered core concepts aligned with the D439 Foundations of Nursing
    learning objectives, including fundamental nursing principles, patient safety,
    evidence-based practice foundations, and professional nursing standards. The format
    was multiple-choice, timed, and required an independent, proctored environment.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Next steps:</strong> Upon receiving confirmation that the quiz requirement
    is satisfied, I will coordinate with my course mentor to schedule the official D439
    objective assessment. In the meantime, I will continue reviewing the course materials
    and use the WGU Nursing Concept Map template (below) to structure my clinical
    documentation throughout D439.
  </p>
</JournalEntry>
